# Mongoose Models

Models live in `DB/<Entity>/`. Connection: `DB/connection.js` → `mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/Suits-app`.

## Schema style

```js
import mongoose from "mongoose";

const entitySchema = new mongoose.Schema(
  {
    field: { type: String, required: true },
    role: { type: String, enum: ["User", "Admin"], default: "User" },
  },
  { timestamps: true }
);

export const Entity = mongoose.model("Entity", entitySchema);
```

## Rules

- Use `timestamps: true` unless there is a clear reason not to
- Export the model as a named export (e.g. `User`, not default)
- Prefer lowercase field names (`email`, `name`) — match the active auth module
- Use `enum` for fixed role/status strings
- Seed scripts (e.g. `seedSuperAdmin.js`) stay next to their model
- Do not embed business logic in schemas; keep it in controllers
